Aditya Dahiya

Greetings, Im Aditya Dahiya. By day, I wrangle bureaucracy, but by night, Im the data wizard conjuring up visual delights and diving deep into health data science. This website is my gallery of creations. So, channel your inner Sherlock and embark on an adventure of discovery! Here are some of my works:

  1. FaNoOp (Facts! Not Opinions!) - my un-opinionated blog on insights from publicly available data.

  2. Presentations and some interesting Projects created by me for random assignments and talks.

  3. Academic books solutions:

    • Solutions Manual of the book R for Data Science (2nd Edition) by Hadley Wickham, Mine etinkaya-Rundel, Garrett Grolemund.

    • Certain Solutions for the Book An Introduction to Statistical Learning: With Applications in R, 1st edition by Daniela Witten, Gareth M. James, Trevor Hastie, Robert Tibshirani.

    • (An in-progress) Solutions Manual and much more for the third edition of ggplot2: Elegant Graphics for Data Analysis (3e) by Hadley Wickham, Danielle Navarro, and Thomas Lin Pedersen.
